  "text": "In this extended abstract, we illustrate the Conflict Packing technique on three parameterized problems. We first obtain a linear vertex-kernel for Feedback Arc Set in Tournaments: while such a kernel was already known to exist [CITATION_1] , our proofs are simpler and shorter. Then we obtain the main result of this paper, namely the first linear vertex-kernel for Dense Rooted Triplet Inconsistency. Finally we apply the technique on Betweenness in Tournaments and obtain a linear vertex-kernel. No polynomial kernel was known before.",
